adjectives.description: capacitated (comparative more capacitated, superlative most capacitated)

entries.meaning: (transitive, mathematics) Constrained by maximum throughput, often applied to physical networks transporting flows.
examples: We consider uniqueness and multiplicity of market equilibria in a short-run setup where traded quantities of electricity are transported through a capacitated network in which power flows have to satisfy the classical lossless DC approximation.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of capacitate
